scree skink
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a South Island skink, distinctive for lateral streaks; lives in dry rocky places such as scree slopes and tussock grasslands.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:Environment
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: <i>Oligosoma waimatense</i>
